[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This one is interesting. This is called Vista 4D and it basically lets you reshoot a video in a different angle and even edit some stuff. This is from Iline Labs and Netflix of all people. So, you'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have a video, it converts into a point cloud and then you can lower the camera in this case. You can basically see the video in a total different perspective.'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Not only that, but you can edit the video. So, you can see here, this is the original shot and this is the point cloud render and they lowered the camera so it seemed like the camera was below'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here, which is actually much nicer. So, it made this sky and the mountains here because they weren\'t there in the original video. You can actually move the camera. So, this is the source'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video, just a little handheld camera, but here they got this moving camera throughout the shot. So, we have more examples. A lot of movement in this shot and even on selfies here, people'

[01:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dancing. But not only that, you can actually edit the video. For example, you can duplicate the car that this couple is standing on. So, they duplicated the car here and this is the'

[01:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'final video. You can also insert this couple, this elder couple, into the scene and then they are here. Very nice. What else we can do? You can make his backpack larger and you can add a cow.'

